# Routing & Navigation

## URL slugs (Vietnamese)

Public routes use Vietnamese slugs: `/tuong`, `/doi-hinh`, `/cong-cu`, `/tin-tuc`, etc. Do not introduce English slugs for new public pages.

## Two shells

| Shell | Layout route | Base path |
|-------|--------------|-----------|
| Public | `src/routes/public-layout.tsx` | `/` |
| Admin | `src/routes/admin-layout.tsx` | `/admin` |

Route tree is defined in [`src/routes.ts`](src/routes.ts). Page components live in `src/pages/`; thin route wrappers live in `src/routes/_pages/` and `src/routes/_redirects/`.

## Adding a public route

Update all of the following:

1. Route wrapper in `src/routes/_pages/my-slug.tsx` (export default from page component)
2. Entry in [`src/routes.ts`](src/routes.ts) under the public layout
3. Static SEO (if list page): add to `STATIC_ROUTE_META` in `src/lib/seo/meta.ts`
4. Dynamic SEO (if detail page): add `loader` + `meta` exports in route wrapper (see `src/lib/seo/loaders.ts`)
5. `NAV_ITEMS` in `src/config/nav.ts` with `labelKey`
6. i18n keys in `src/locales/{vi,en}/nav.json`

Example route wrapper:

```tsx
import { staticPageMeta } from "@/lib/seo/meta"

export const meta = staticPageMeta("/my-slug", "Page Name")
export { MyFeaturePage as default } from "@/pages/MyFeaturePage"
```

## Adding an admin route

1. Route wrapper in `src/routes/_pages/admin-my-slug.tsx`
2. Entry in `src/routes.ts` under the admin layout
3. `meta` via `adminStaticMeta()` from `src/lib/seo/loaders.ts`
4. Item in `ADMIN_NAV` (`src/components/AdminSidebar.tsx`)

## Code splitting

React Router v7 Framework Mode splits routes automatically from `src/routes.ts`. Do **not** add manual `React.lazy()` wrappers.

## Legacy redirects

When renaming trait routes, add redirect route modules under `src/routes/_redirects/` — never break old URLs silently.
